  "prompt": "Who was the first teacher in the world?",
  "response": "The concept of a \"first teacher\" in the world is difficult to pinpoint historically because teaching in its most basic form likely existed before recorded history, even among early human communities and other species through social learning and imitation. If we consider formal education, ancient civilizations such as Sumer, Egypt, and China had teachers. In myth or legend, figures like Thoth in Egyptian mythology and Confucius in Chinese history are often associated with early teaching and wisdom, but none of these can be definitively called the \"first teacher.\" Teaching likely evolved naturally as a part of early human development.",
